## 3. {{AGENTS}} — delegation by capability

Delegate focused work to a specialist rather than doing everything in one
context. Each specialist has a single clear purpose and a defined output
contract. Specs live in [`{{DIR_AGENTS}}/`]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/).

| {{AGENT}} | Use it when… |
| --- | --- |
| [reviewer]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/reviewer.md) | a change is ready and needs a correctness + quality pass before merge |
| [tester]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/tester.md) | you need tests written, run, or a failure diagnosed |
| [architect]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/architect.md) | a task needs a design/plan before any code is written |
| [docs]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/docs.md) | code is done and user-facing docs/READMEs must follow |
| [security]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/security.md) | a change touches auth, input handling, secrets, or dependencies |
| [explorer]({{DIR_AGENTS}}/explorer.md) | you must sweep many files for an answer but only want the conclusion |

**Rule of delegation:** read-only investigation can be dispatched freely; any
{{AGENT}} that *writes* must return a summary of exactly what it changed.

---

## 4. {{SKILLS}} — repeatable workflows

A {{SKILL}} is a written procedure for a recurring task. Run the matching {{SKILL}}
before improvising. Specs live in [`{{DIR_SKILLS}}/`]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/).

| {{SKILL}} | Trigger |
| --- | --- |
| [plan]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/plan.md) | a task has more than a couple of steps |
| [verify]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/verify.md) | about to claim something is done |
| [repo-map]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/repo-map.md) | orienting to the repo, or structure changed |
| [commit]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/commit.md) | staging and writing a commit |
| [code-review]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/code-review.md) | reviewing a diff or PR |
| [create-skill]({{DIR_SKILLS}}/create-skill.md) | a task has crystallised into a repeatable pattern |

When a task repeats and no {{SKILL}} covers it, forge one (see `create-skill`).

---

## 5. {{MEMORY}} — durable knowledge across sessions

Persistent facts live in [`{{DIR_MEMORY}}/`]({{DIR_MEMORY}}/) — one fact per file, indexed by a
local `MEMORY.md`. Read that index at the start of a session; write a new memory
whenever the conversation yields a durable fact, a correction, or a decision
worth keeping. The `{{DIR_MEMORY}}/` directory is **personal and git-ignored** — it is
never committed or shared; to share knowledge, put it in code, docs, or the
project {{LAWS}}. Full convention: [`{{DIR_MEMORY}}/README.md`]({{DIR_MEMORY}}/README.md).

---

## 6. {{SCRIPTS}} — optional automation

Everything above works on agent self-discipline alone. For teams that want hard
automation, the `rituals/` directory ships a dependency-free CLI (`harness build`,
`harness learn`, `harness doctor`) you can wire to git hooks or CI. It is opt-in —
the harness is fully functional without it.
